{
  "text": "The system presented here works on a similar principle to that of [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] , in that it utilizes the Fresnel reflection from a window placed in the path of the illumination beam to produce a reference beam. However, in our approach no mechanical phase stepping is required. The system is used with a semiconductor laser diode which is held at a fixed wavelength using temperature and current controllers. Modulation of the control current and/or temperature results in a variation in the output wavelength. This causes a change of phase in the interferometer Δϕ, which is dependent on the pathlength imbalance Δl (twice the separation between the object and the window) and is given by [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] ",
  "correct_citation": {
